{"parse":{"title":"White v Chief Constable of the South Yorkshire Police","pageid":36307059,"revid":847284734,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><i><b>White v Chief Constable of the South Yorkshire Police</b></i> was a 1998 case in <a href=\"/wiki/English_tort_law\" title=\"English tort law\">English tort law</a> in which police officers who were present in the aftermath of the <a href=\"/wiki/Hillsborough_disaster\" title=\"Hillsborough disaster\">Hillsborough disaster</a> sued for post traumatic stress disorder. The claim was rejected by the House of Lords on the basis that none of the claimants could be considered \"primary victims\" \"since none of them were at any time exposed to personal danger nor reasonably believed themselves to be so\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The decision could have been disposed of in the manner of <a href=\"/wiki/Chadwick_v_British_Railways_Board\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Chadwick v British Railways Board\">Chadwick v British Railways Board</a>, where the rescuer may not have been in physical danger but was awarded damages due to his putting himself in the 'zone of danger', after the event. This was not followed and the \"rescuers\" category was thus limited in terms of people acting in the course of their job.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=White_v_Chief_Constable_of_the_South_Yorkshire_Police&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Alcock_v_Chief_Constable_of_South_Yorkshire_Police\" title=\"Alcock v Chief Constable of South Yorkshire Police\">Alcock v Chief Constable of South Yorkshire Police</a></i></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=White_v_Chief_Constable_of_the_South_Yorkshire_Police&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://sixthformlaw.info/02_cases/mod3a/aqa/_cases_tort_1duty.htm#White%20and%20others%20v%20Chief%20Constable%20of%20South%20Yorkshire%20and%20others%20%5B1999%5D%20HL\">\"White and others v Chief Constable of South Yorkshire and others %5B1998%5D HL\"</a>. sixthformlaw.info<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">27 February</span> 2013</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=White+and+others+v+Chief+Constable+of+South+Yorkshire+and+others+%255B1998%255D+HL&amp;rft.pub=sixthformlaw.info&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fsixthformlaw.info%2F02_cases%2Fmod3a%2Faqa%2F_cases_tort_1duty.htm%23White%2520and%2520others%2520v%2520Chief%2520Constable%2520of%2520South%2520Yorkshire%2520and%2520others%2520%255B1999%255D%2520HL&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWhite+v+Chief+Constable+of+the+South+Yorkshire+Police\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=White_v_Chief_Constable_of_the_South_Yorkshire_Police&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"no